message: Determine which eyebrow is more dominant. Before beginning your training, you will want to figure out which eyebrow will be most easily trained. Typically, this will be your dominant eyebrow. Stand in front of a mirror, and try to lift your right eyebrow. Then try to lift only your left eyebrow. [CHECKSUM: determine-which-eyebrow-dominant.-before]

>

You will start by trying to make one eyebrow slightly higher than the other. If you are having trouble with this, think about where your eyes naturally look when you see something interesting or exciting. That is usually where your attention is drawn. You may find it easier to focus on the eye that attracts the most attention.

# Overview

In this lab we will create a simple Go program that can be run from a browser.  This is similar to what we did in [Lab 3](/lab/labs/lab03), but instead of using a web framework such as Django, Flask or Ruby on Rails, we'll use the built-in HTTP server and a static file server.

Our web server will serve up static files: images, CSS stylesheets and JavaScripts. It will also respond to requests for dynamically-generated HTML pages. Since our dynamic content will be generated by Go, it makes sense to name our app `go`.
